-- Regression (#23): a HOF generalized to `(Num a, Num b) =>` from literals applied
-- INSIDE its body (`app2 f = f 2 3`), called with a function that ties those Num
-- vars to ANOTHER class (Eq) and yields a concrete result whose own type is
-- discarded (`main : Unit`).  The Num var is grounded by neither an argument nor the
-- caller's result, so it is genuinely ambiguous and MUST default to Int (PLAN #11).
-- Before the fix the callee's Num dict route resolved RNone тАФ a NULL dict word тЖТ
-- `inttoptr 0; load` build-time SIGTRAP тАФ while `medaka run` was correct (runтЙаbuild).
-- Root cause: the INFERRED constraint's iface was lost ("") because
-- `ifaceForConstraintId` only reads a bare-`TVar` obligation occ, but a `fromInt`/
-- method-site constraint records a COMPOUND occ; recovered from `schemeObligations`
-- (own-body literal) and the forwarded `pendingDictApps` slot (transitive `useApp`).
-- Each println must print its run-identical value (all `2 == 3` тЗТ False).
app2 f = f 2 3
useIt h = h 2 3
eqBoth a b = a == b
useApp g = app2 g

main =
  println (app2 (==))
  println (useIt eqBoth)
  println (app2 (x y => x == y))
  println (useApp (==))
